<%# The five-state status (and #146's badge menu) is gone — visibility is
    the only state, toggled by the visibility button; the type reads as the
    file icon next to the title.

    Two deliberate bands, both broadcast-safe (derive from the plan alone):
      1. Title row — icon + title, with the save bookmark flowing inline
         after the title's last word so it lands sensibly on every wrap.
      2. Meta row — byline on the left, live presence on the right,
         indented to the title's text column so it reads as one block. %>
<%# data-plan-visibility is the authoritative state flag: the visibility
    toggle (outside this partial — it's policy-gated) watches header
    replacements and mirrors this value, so API publishes and other tabs
    keep the button honest. %>
<div class="page-header page-header--plan" id="plan-header" data-plan-visibility="<%= plan.visibility %>">
  <div class="page-header__title-row">
    <%= plan_type_icon(plan, size: :lg) %>
    <h1 class="page-header__title"><%= plan.title %><%# The save bookmark mounts here from outside this partial: it's
          viewer-relative (needs current_user), and this header re-renders
          from broadcasts where there is none — plan_bookmark_controller
          re-stamps it after every replace. Inside the h1 so it trails the
          last word of the title, wherever wrapping puts it. %><span id="plan-bookmark-slot" class="plan-bookmark-slot"></span></h1>
  </div>
  <div class="page-header__meta">
    <div class="page-header__byline text-sm text-muted">
      <%= user_avatar(plan.created_by_user) %> <%= profile_link(plan.created_by_user) %> · v<%= plan.current_revision %><%= plan_state_badge(plan) %>
      <%# A tag on someone's plan reads as "find more like this", not "filter
          my workspace" (which is what the row chips in YOUR workspace do) —
          so it's a search, org-wide. search_text indexes tag names. %>
      <% plan.tags.each do |tag| %>
        <%= link_to tag.name, search_path(q: tag.name), class: "badge badge--tag",
              title: "Search plans tagged “#{tag.name}”" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <%= render partial: "coplan/plans/viewers", locals: { viewers: CoPlan::PlanViewer.active_viewers_for(plan), current_user: current_user } %>
  </div>
</div>
